To fix the "Database error deleting user" issue and improve the SQL structure, I have created a new file named `supabase_setup.sql` in your project.

This file contains the complete, improved SQL script. You can copy the contents of this file and paste it into the **Supabase SQL Editor** to reset your table with the correct "Cascade Delete" rules (which allows users to be deleted without error) and security policies.

# Updated files:

## supabase_setup.sql

Created a comprehensive SQL script to set up the database table correctly.

```sql
-- Run this entire script in the Supabase SQL Editor.
-- It recreates the table with "ON DELETE CASCADE" to fix the deletion error.

-- 1. Reset Table (WARNING: This clears existing data to ensure clean state)
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS public.user_data;

-- 2. Create Table with Cascade Delete
-- "ON DELETE CASCADE" automatically removes the user's data when the user account is deleted.
CREATE TABLE public.user_data (
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY,
  data JSONB,
  updated_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT timezone('utc'::text, now())
);

-- 3. Enable Security
ALTER TABLE public.user_data ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- 4. Add Access Policies
CREATE POLICY "Users can view their own data" ON public.user_data FOR SELECT USING (auth.uid() = user_id);
CREATE POLICY "Users can insert their own data" ON public.user_data FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);
CREATE POLICY "Users can update their own data" ON public.user_data FOR UPDATE USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

